as a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh de Grove Hercy was born in 1300, in Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Alicia. He died in 1367, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1300–1367":"1300–1367","1305–1340":"1305–1340","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1305":"1305","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","1340":"1340","1328":"1328","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Grove, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Grove, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1300–1367":"1300–1367","1305–1340":"1305–1340","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1305":"1305","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","1340":"1340","1328":"1328","about 1340":"noin 1340","Grove, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Grove, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1300–1367":"1300–1367","1305–1340":"1305–1340","1328–1378":"1328–1378","1305":"